                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#56vb">Fol. 56vb</locus>: Ownership note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 56vb: በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘአባእኮ፡ ዘደብረ፡ </q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 56vb: In the name of the Father, the Son and the Holy Spirit. This book is of Däbrä ʾAbaʾǝko. </q>
                           The note is written in a crude hand. The name of the church of ʾAbaǝʾko is attested in other Mss. of Mǝdrä Ruba, e.g., MR-012, MR-012. It seems to be one of several churches in the area which disappeared, but whose tabots and books were brought to the church of Mǝdrä Ruba.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#81rb">Fol. 81rb</locus>: Protective prayer for healing wounds.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 81rb: ጸሎተ፡ ቍስል፡ ሰተናዊ፡ ቀተናዊ፡ ወግድ፡ አምላክ፡... </q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Crude and minor notes: fols. 1r, 1v, 8v, 11r, 13r, 28v, 39v, 78r, 81v.&#xD;
- Crude uncolored ornamental bands on fols. 8v, 81r.&#xD;
- Spaces for rubricated names left unfilled throughout the supplication formula: e.g., fols. 2rb, 9rb, 9vb, 10ra, 12ra, 13vb, 14ra, 14vb, 15ra.&#xD;
- The scribe used compressed script on fols. 53va-54vb, 81ra-rb.</item>
                     </list>
